== English ==

=== Etymology ===
[[Japanese]] deko (''uneven'') + ponkan (''one of the parent fruits'')

=== Noun ===
{{wikipedia}}
'''dekopon'''
#A [[hybrid]] citrus fruit made from crossing a ChungGyun [[mandarin]] and a [[ponkan]]. They are quite large and have a [[sweet]] taste.

